Captions:
Andhra Pradesh has made a triumphant return to the international arena with its prominent presence at the World Economic Forum 2025 in Davos. Spearheaded by Chief Minister Nara Chandrababu Naidu and IT & HRD Minister Nara Lokesh, the state showcased its commitment to innovation, growth, and global collaboration. 
Under the visionary leadership of Naidu, known for his forward-thinking policies and transformative initiatives, Andhra Pradesh highlighted its readiness to attract investments and foster partnerships across key sectors like technology, renewable energy, infrastructure, and healthcare. Nara Lokesh, representing the new generation of leadership, engaged with global investors and thought leaders, emphasising the state's thriving IT ecosystem, skilled workforce, and investor-friendly policies.
